is RZ, Christians U, et al. "Red wine decreases cyclosporine bioavailability." Clin Pharmacol Ther 70 (2001): 462-7[18] Yee GC, Stanley DL, Pessa LJ, et al. "Effect of grrapefruit juice on blood cyclosporin concentration." Lancet 345 (1995): 955-6[19] Ioannidesdemos LL, Christophidis N, Ryan P, Angelis P, Liolios L, Mclean AJ "Dosing implications of a clinical interaction between grapefruit juice and cyclosporine and metabolite concentrations in patients with autoimmune diseases." J Rheumatol 24 (1997): 49-54[20] Oliveira-Freitas VL, Dalla Costa T, Manfro RC, Cruz LB, Schwartsmann G "Influence of purple grape juice in cyclosporine availability." J Ren Nutr 20 (2010): 309-13[21] Tan KKC, Trull AK, Uttridge JA, Metcalfe S, Heyes CS, Facey S, Evans DB "Effect of dietary fat on the pharmacokinetics and pharmacodynamics of cyclosporine in kidney transplant recipients." Clin Pharmacol Ther 57 (1995): 425-33[22] Hollander AAMJ, Vanrooij J, Lentjes EGWM, Arbouw F, Vanbree JB, Schoemaker RC, Vanes LA, Vanderwoude FJ, Cohen AF "The effect of grapefruit juice on cyclosporine and prednisone metabolism in transplant patients." Clin Pharmacol Ther 57 (1995): 318-24[23] Ducharme MP, Provenzano R, Dehoornesmith M, Edwards DJ "Trough concentrations of cyclosporine in blood following administration with grapefruit juice." Br J Clin Pharmacol 36 (1993): 457-9[24] Cerner Multum, Inc. "Australian Product Information." O 0[25] Bailey DG, Malcolm J, Arnold O, Spence JD "Grapefruit juice-drug interactions." Br J Clin Pharmacol 46 (1998): 101-10[26] Cerner Multum, Inc. "UK Summary of Product Characteristics." O 0[27] Kupferschmidt HHT, Fattinger KE, Ha HR, Follath F, Krahenbuhl S "Grapefruit juice enhances the bioavailability of the HIV protease inhibitor saquinavir in man." Br J Clin Pharmacol 45 (1998): 355-9[28] Eagling VA, Profit L, Back DJ "Inhibition of the CYP3A4-mediated metabolism and P-glycoprotein-mediated transport of the HIV-I protease inhibitor saquinavir by grapefruit juice c