glutide, Empagliflozin, Dulaglutide, Canagliflozin, Dapagliflozin, Fenofibric acid, Mipomersen, More', 'Acalabrutinib, Dacomitinib, Tepotinib, Avapritinib, Bosutinib, Vemurafenib, Selumetinib, Vandetanib, Cobimetinib, Capmatinib, Ibrutinib, More', 'Moderate', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/77827/', '[1] "Product Information. Tafinlar (dabrafenib)." GlaxoSmithKline, Research Triangle Park, NC.[2] Cerner Multum, Inc. "UK Summary of Product Characteristics." O 0[3] Cerner Multum, Inc. "Australian Product Information." O 0[4] Richter WO, Jacob BG, Schwandt P "Interaction between fibre and lovastatin." Lancet 338 (1991): 706[5] Lilja JJ, Kivisto KT, Neuvonen PJ "Grapefruit juice-simvastatin interaction: Effect on serum concentrations of simvastatin, simvastatin acid, and HMG-CoA reductase inhibitors." Clin Pharmacol Ther 64 (1998): 477-83[6] Kantola T, Kivisto KT, Neuvonen PJ "Grapefruit juice greatly increases serum concentrations of lovastatin and lovastatin acid." Clin Pharmacol Ther 63 (1998): 397-402[7] "Product Information. Mevacor (lovastatin)." Merck & Co, Inc, West Point, PA.[8] Bailey DG, Malcolm J, Arnold O, Spence JD "Grapefruit juice-drug interactions." Br J Clin Pharmacol 46 (1998): 101-10[9] Neuvonen PJ, Backman JT, Niemi M "Pharmacokinetic comparison of the potential over-the-counter statins simvastatin, lovastatin, fluvastatin and pravastatin." Clin Pharmacokinet 47 (2008): 463-74[10] Thompson PD, Clarkson P, Karas RH "Statin-associated myopathy." JAMA 289 (2003): 1681-90[11] "Product Information. Zocor (simvastatin)." Merck & Co, Inc, West Point, PA.[12] "Product Information. Tafinlar (dabrafenib)." GlaxoSmithKline, Research Triangle Park, NC.', 1767369485);
